<big><b>The Vikings - History Text</b></big>

<big><b>THE VIKINGS</b></big>

The Vikings were people from Scandinavia.

They lived in northern Europe more than 1,000 years ago.

Today, Scandinavia includes:

• Norway
• Sweden
• Denmark

The Vikings became famous for their ships, exploration, and trading.


<big><b>Viking Ships</b></big>

The Vikings built long and narrow ships called <b>longships</b>.

These ships were fast and could travel across oceans and rivers.

Examples:

• Vikings sailed to England and France.
• They explored Iceland and Greenland.
• Some Vikings reached North America.


<big><b>Viking Warriors</b></big>

Many Vikings were warriors.

They traveled to other lands in search of wealth and new opportunities.

Examples:

• Warriors carried swords and shields.
• They protected their villages.
• Some Vikings became famous leaders.


<big><b>Daily Life</b></big>

Most Vikings were not warriors.

They worked as:

• Farmers
• Fishermen
• Blacksmiths
• Merchants

Examples:

• Farmers grew crops and raised animals.
• Fishermen provided food for their communities.
• Merchants traded goods with distant regions.


<big><b>Religion and Beliefs</b></big>

Before becoming Christians, Vikings believed in many gods.

Some important gods were:

• Odin – god of wisdom
• Thor – god of thunder
• Freyja – goddess of love

Examples:

• Vikings told stories about their gods.
• These stories were passed from generation to generation.


<big><b>Trade and Exploration</b></big>

The Vikings were skilled traders.

They exchanged goods with many different cultures.

Some products they traded were:

• Fur
• Silver
• Iron
• Amber

Examples:

• Trade brought wealth to Viking communities.
• New ideas spread through trade routes.


<big><b>Interesting Facts</b></big>

• Vikings were excellent sailors.
• They used the stars to help navigate.
• The Viking Age lasted about 300 years.
• Some English words come from the Viking language.


